{"_id":"uehjQcoyKy0qZN61","name":"Athletics","type":"skill","img":"icons/skills/movement/feet-winged-boots-brown.webp","data":{"difficulty":"basic","type":"move","cost":{"trained":"200","plus10":"400","plus20":"600"},"stat":{"str":true,"tou":false,"agi":true,"wfr":false,"wfm":false,"int":false,"per":false,"cr":false,"ch":false,"ld":false},"description":"<p>Athletics is the acrobatic and tactical movement skill that allows characters to make balanced and poised movement. Athletics have two sections: Agility- and Strength-based movement.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>STRENGTH:</strong> Athletics Strength is a character's ability to climb, swim, and other strength-based physical activities.</li>\n<li><strong>AGILITY:</strong> Athletics Agility is a character's ability to balance, jump, catch landings, and move about a battlefield or training course.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Athletics Concealment</h2>\n<p>Another use for Athletics Agility is to move silently amongst the battlefield. If a character is attempting to move silently, they roll Athletics. For every degree of success, the opponents gain a -5 on their hearing check.</p>","characteristic":{},"data":{"description":"<p>This is the description.</p>"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"an9AAnyv69VtBEmg":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.k913vheZuFYJxB2g"}}}
{"_id":"J1pujf3vq2l9bNpL","name":"Appeal","type":"skill","img":"icons/skills/social/peace-luck-insult.webp","data":{"difficulty":"basic","type":"social","cost":{"trained":"200","plus10":"400","plus20":"600"},"stat":{"str":false,"tou":false,"agi":false,"wfr":false,"wfm":false,"int":false,"per":false,"cr":false,"ch":true,"ld":false},"description":"<p>Appeal is a talent of charm and social abilities. Appealing allows players and characters to sway the reactions of others with well-meaning words and facial expressions. A character with the Appeal Skill can attempt to alter any social interactions. Appeal can be used to attempt to change a character's opinions and to convince characters and players to attempt something else.</p>\n<p>When Appeal is used against someone, it is an Opposed Test, which is opposed by Interrogation (Courage).</p>\n<table style=\"width: 98.6248%; height: 144px;\" border=\"1\">\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<th style=\"width: 15.8429%; height: 16px;\">MOD</th>\n<th style=\"width: 83.7587%; height: 16px;\">EXAMPLE</th>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 15.8429%; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">+30</td>\n<td style=\"width: 83.7587%; height: 16px; text-align: left;\">The character is already devoted or incredibly friendly to the character making the test.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 15.8429%; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">+20</td>\n<td style=\"width: 83.7587%; height: 16px; text-align: left;\">The character is friendly with the character attempting the test.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 15.8429%; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">+10</td>\n<td style=\"width: 83.7587%; height: 16px; text-align: left;\">The character is a part of the same squad or commanding unit.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 15.8429%; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">0</td>\n<td style=\"width: 83.7587%; height: 16px; text-align: left;\">The character does not care or has nothing in common.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 15.8429%; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">-10</td>\n<td style=\"width: 83.7587%; height: 16px; text-align: left;\">The character does not want to be bothered.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 15.8429%; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">-20</td>\n<td style=\"width: 83.7587%; height: 16px; text-align: left;\">The character is suspicious or had bad interactions with the character attempting the test.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 15.8429%; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">-30</td>\n<td style=\"width: 83.7587%; height: 16px; text-align: left;\">The character is hostile.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 15.8429%; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">-60</td>\n<td style=\"width: 83.7587%; height: 16px; text-align: left;\">The character is an enemy with no intention of listening.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"an9AAnyv69VtBEmg":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.Uc37CQGI8Snirror"}}}
{"name":"Deception","type":"skill","img":"icons/skills/social/theft-pickpocket-bribery-brown.webp","data":{"difficulty":"basic","type":"social","cost":{"trained":"200","plus10":"400","plus20":"600"},"stat":{"str":false,"tou":false,"agi":false,"wfr":false,"wfm":false,"int":false,"per":false,"cr":false,"ch":true,"ld":false},"description":"<p>The Deception Skill is when a character attempts to lie to a character or player. A character using this Skill attempts to lie. Examples of using the Deception Skill:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Attempting to disguise an item. This is different from Camouflage as you aren't attempting to hide the item, but you are trying to trick someone that it is something else.</li>\n<li>Attempting to distract someone. This could be by keeping someone's attention or lying of something to quickly move the opponent's eye from what is actually happening. This can be used as a Sleight of Hand.</li>\n<li>To tell someone orders, but to twist the words to show another meaning.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Deception skill is opposed by an opponent's Investigation. Deception also follows the same modifier example as listed under @Compendium[world.skills.J1pujf3vq2l9bNpL]{Appeal}.</p>"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"an9AAnyv69VtBEmg":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.bwyYVWpjg31YYUru"}},"_id":"0AjLYGJlgIzz4WAO"}
{"name":"Demolition","type":"skill","img":"icons/magic/fire/explosion-embers-orange.webp","data":{"difficulty":"adv","type":"field","cost":{"trained":"200","plus10":"400","plus20":"600"},"stat":{"str":false,"tou":false,"agi":false,"wfr":false,"wfm":false,"int":true,"per":false,"cr":false,"ch":false,"ld":false},"description":"<p>The Demolition Skill allows characters to utilize explosives in whatever situation needed. The character with proper Demolition knowledge knows how much explosive needed to take something out. Using Demolition also covers manufacturing explosives at a modest penalty (usually around -20). The Demolition Skill can also allow a character to defuse and disarm explosives at an Opposed Test against whoever set up the explosive.</p>"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"an9AAnyv69VtBEmg":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.zDWVVRP6LFHLS917"}},"_id":"Wt1PTE8MWyDD5KlU"}
{"name":"Evasion","type":"skill","img":"icons/magic/fire/explosion-embers-evade-silhouette.webp","data":{"difficulty":"basic","type":"move","cost":{"trained":"200","plus10":"400","plus20":"600"},"stat":{"str":false,"tou":false,"agi":true,"wfr":false,"wfm":false,"int":false,"per":false,"cr":false,"ch":false,"ld":false},"description":"<p>The Evasion skill is the act of dodging and parrying attacks as a Reaction. Evasion is used when an attack is made against the character. Evasion can also be used when avoiding environmental dangers. A character can make an Evasion Test with each attack made against the character. With each Evasion Test made in the same Round, the next test gains a -10 Penalty. These Penalties stack, so the first Evasion will be at a basic Evasion Test, the second roll will be at a -10 Penalty, and the third at a -20, and so on. The more tests made, the more the character scrambles and attempts to dodge peppering fire or close-combat assaults.</p>\n<p>When making Evasion Tests away from an area of effect damage or something falling, or anything that would call for those to jump or run out of the way frantically, the Character may make an Evasion Test. For every Degree of Success made, the character is able to Evade up to 2 Meters, up to their Charge Movement distance.</p>"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"an9AAnyv69VtBEmg":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.Cyx87N7oXrkUAnBw"}},"_id":"euCPGPHnY8sFWok9"}
{"name":"Gambling","type":"skill","img":"icons/sundries/gaming/dice-pair-white-green.webp","data":{"difficulty":"basic","type":"social","cost":{"trained":"0","plus10":"0","plus20":"0"},"stat":{"str":false,"tou":false,"agi":false,"wfr":false,"wfm":false,"int":true,"per":false,"cr":false,"ch":true,"ld":false},"description":"<p>The Gambling Skill is used to deal with any sort of gaming and betting. Even in war, characters need something to do on their off times or when held up in bad situations.</p>\n<p>Each participant in the game can bet an amount and then make Opposed Tests with the Gamble Skill. The character with the most degrees of success wins. **Deception** can be used to cheat, such as pulling cards. If the Deception is successful, for every two degrees of success on the Deception adds +10 to the Gambling Skill roll.</p>"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"an9AAnyv69VtBEmg":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.hv0I8liw8kUb5z5i"}},"_id":"iGeydoUQX57SflmS"}
{"_id":"iGeydoUQX57SflmS","name":"Gambling","type":"skill","img":"icons/sundries/gaming/dice-pair-white-green.webp","data":{"difficulty":"basic","type":"social","cost":{"trained":"0","plus10":"0","plus20":"0"},"stat":{"str":false,"tou":false,"agi":false,"wfr":false,"wfm":false,"int":true,"per":false,"cr":false,"ch":true,"ld":false},"description":"<p>The Gambling Skill is used to deal with any sort of gaming and betting. Even in war, characters need something to do on their off times or when held up in bad situations.</p>\n<p>Each participant in the game can bet an amount and then make Opposed Tests with the Gamble Skill. The character with the most degrees of success wins. @Compendium[world.skills.0AjLYGJlgIzz4WAO]{Deception}&nbsp;can be used to cheat, such as pulling cards. If the Deception is successful, for every two degrees of success on the Deception adds +10 to the Gambling Skill roll.</p>"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"an9AAnyv69VtBEmg":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.hv0I8liw8kUb5z5i"}}}
{"name":"Interrogation","type":"skill","img":"icons/commodities/metal/chain-steel.webp","data":{"difficulty":"basic","type":"social","cost":{"trained":"200","plus10":"400","plus20":"600"},"stat":{"str":false,"tou":false,"agi":false,"wfr":false,"wfm":false,"int":true,"per":false,"cr":true,"ch":false,"ld":true},"description":"<p>Interrogation allows a character to extort information from an opponent with both mental and physical means. The GM may modify the Difficulty of the Interrogation Test according to the character's trainings and tools being used by the characters making the test.</p>\n<p>Interrogation is an Opposed Test with the opponent's Courage or Charisma Characteristic. If the opponent wins the Opposed Test, the interrogator gets nothing worthwhile. If the interrogators win the opposed test, every degree of success gets either another answer, or the answer becomes clearer. An Interrogation can be retried with a failure, but each time a test fails, it takes twice as long and the next test gains a -10 penalty.</p>"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"an9AAnyv69VtBEmg":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.CsBuybGytcmfcC6O"}},"_id":"F8NscYjob1fNot3U"}
{"name":"Intimidation","type":"skill","img":"icons/skills/social/intimidation-impressing.webp","data":{"difficulty":"basic","type":"social","cost":{"trained":"200","plus10":"400","plus20":"600"},"stat":{"str":true,"tou":false,"agi":false,"wfr":false,"wfm":false,"int":true,"per":false,"cr":false,"ch":true,"ld":true},"description":"<p>Intimidation is one of the few special Skills that can use many Characteristics. Players can use Strength, Charisma, Leadership, and Intellect to force and scare their opponent to give in to demands.</p>\n<p>Intimidation is an opposed test. The opponent uses the same set of Characteristics to Oppose the test.</p>\n<p>A character must not just choose their highest Characteristic to use the Intimidation. The Characteristic used must fit the situation that the Intimidation is being used in.</p>"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"an9AAnyv69VtBEmg":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.yU64IFUrvfieivaZ"}},"_id":"PuQCrNcG9znjLGFZ"}
{"name":"Investigation","type":"skill","img":"icons/tools/scribal/magnifying-glass.webp","data":{"difficulty":"basic","type":"social","cost":{"trained":"0","plus10":"0","plus20":"0"},"stat":{"str":false,"tou":false,"agi":false,"wfr":false,"wfm":false,"int":true,"per":true,"cr":false,"ch":false,"ld":false},"description":"<p>Investigation covers many sections in 100DOS. Make sure to pay attention as to see how and what Investigation covers.</p>\n<p>Investigation can cover the use of gaining information by asking questions, starting conversations, and eavesdropping. This part of Investigation focuses on information from larger groups of characters. The better the Degrees of Success, the more information is gained.</p>\n<p>Investigation allows the character to visually understand and be aware of their surroundings. This is used when trying to find hidden objects. When attempting to find an object, only a straight Perception based Investigation Test needs to be rolled. If a character has hidden the item (or himself), then the test becomes Opposed against the opponent's Camouflage Skill.</p>"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"an9AAnyv69VtBEmg":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.icEKEN2nvwICmxst"}},"_id":"90Bjg0xEU9HrLQJQ"}
{"name":"Medication (Human)","type":"skill","img":"icons/skills/wounds/injury-stapled-flesh-tan.webp","data":{"difficulty":"adv","type":"field","cost":{"trained":"300","plus10":"500","plus20":"700"},"stat":{"str":false,"tou":false,"agi":false,"wfr":false,"wfm":false,"int":true,"per":false,"cr":false,"ch":false,"ld":false},"description":"<p>Medication is the general skill of being a medic and having knowledge of biological and medical sciences. Learning proper medical skills takes time, so the GM may choose how long it will take. An effective time to allow Characters to learn the Medical Skill is between missions when the Characters have downtime.</p>\n<p>A character with the Medication Skill can diagnose symptoms, apply first aid, and reduce a Character's Wounds and Fatigue.</p>\n<p>This Skill relies heavily on Medical Tools. Surgeries cannot be done without the proper tools, wounds cannot be bandaged without bandages or cloth, and medication cannot be given if it is not owned.</p>\n<h2>First Aid</h2>\n<p>The Medication Skill can be used to perform First Aid Actions, which are Extended Actions. There are two types of First Aid: Fatigue Aid and Wound Aid. These Actions can only be taken if the Character has a Medical Kit and the Medication Skill at Trained, or better. No Skill Test is needed.</p>\n<p>Fatigue Aid reduces Fatigue by 1 level for every minute of the First Aid Action that's given. When used with Fatigue lowering Medical Equipment, the Medic adds half their Intellect Modifier to the Fatigue lowered.</p>\n<p>Wound Aid removes Wounds by 1 per every hour of First Aid Action that's given. The Medic may use Biofoam alongside this and increase the Biofoam's healing by half their Intellect Modifier per use. This does not count as the Extended Medical Test needed to allow the patient to begin healing normally and does not reset the uses of Biofoam the Character may receive.</p>\n<p>When given proper equipment, the Medic may have multiple patients at a time that they give these First Aid Extended Actions to. A Character giving First Aid may have up to their Intellect Modifier in Patients that they tend to at a time, without increasing how long it takes to care for everyone involved.</p>\n<h2>Diagnoses</h2>\n<p>With a successful Medication Skill Test, a Medic can diagnose a disease or medical issue. The GM can alter the difficulty of the test for different situations. If a bullet wound causes the issue, it would be a Simple Medical Test. A well known disease could be a +20. The GM may come up with the Difficulty Modifier needed to pass the Diagnosis.</p>\n<p>Each time a Character makes a proper Diagnosis, the next time they come across the same medical issue, they gain a stacking +10 Bonus. Once the character would reach +40 to their Diagnosis Test, they are considered to pass the test automatically.</p>\n<h2>Extended Medical Test</h2>\n<p>The Medication Skill and a Medical Kit is needed to do an Extended Medical Test, where the Character cares for their patient to hasten their healing process and recover from the usage of various drugs, such as Biofoam. Extended Medical Tests take 4 Hours, but is reduced by 1 hour per Degree of Success on a Medication Test, to a minimum of 1. Degrees of Failure will each add an etra 30 Minutes onto the Action.</p>\n<p>The Character who receives an Extended Medical Test will have their natural healing increased. Every 24 hours, the Character will heal their Toughness Modifier worth of Wounds. The Medication Test also increases the number of wounds healed on the first day by the amount of Degrees of Success the Medic rolled.</p>\n<p>Characters who receive Extended Medical Tests will continue to receive them each day, up to the Medic's Intellect Modifier in days, but only if they rest. Characters who take actions such as Charge, Run, or Full Actions of Attacks will lose the next following days of the Extended Medical Test.</p>\n<h2>Alien Biology</h2>\n<p>There are many races, most of which share a completely alien biology compared to each other. Any Medication Tests made against an alien, without the proper Skill, is at a -60, including the Untrained Penalty.</p>"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"an9AAnyv69VtBEmg":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.L4PHbmHHayXYgkaA"}},"_id":"H1CpKJ3ST9BXREu8"}
{"name":"Medication (Covenant)","type":"skill","img":"icons/skills/wounds/injury-stitched-flesh-red.webp","data":{"difficulty":"adv","type":"field","cost":{"trained":"300","plus10":"500","plus20":"700"},"stat":{"str":false,"tou":false,"agi":false,"wfr":false,"wfm":false,"int":true,"per":false,"cr":false,"ch":false,"ld":false},"description":"<p>Medication is the general skill of being a medic and having knowledge of biological and medical sciences. Learning proper medical skills takes time, so the GM may choose how long it will take. An effective time to allow Characters to learn the Medical Skill is between missions when the Characters have downtime.</p>\n<p>A character with the Medication Skill can diagnose symptoms, apply first aid, and reduce a Character's Wounds and Fatigue.</p>\n<p>This Skill relies heavily on Medical Tools. Surgeries cannot be done without the proper tools, wounds cannot be bandaged without bandages or cloth, and medication cannot be given if it is not owned.</p>\n<h2>First Aid</h2>\n<p>The Medication Skill can be used to perform First Aid Actions, which are Extended Actions. There are two types of First Aid: Fatigue Aid and Wound Aid. These Actions can only be taken if the Character has a Medical Kit and the Medication Skill at Trained, or better. No Skill Test is needed.</p>\n<p>Fatigue Aid reduces Fatigue by 1 level for every minute of the First Aid Action that's given. When used with Fatigue lowering Medical Equipment, the Medic adds half their Intellect Modifier to the Fatigue lowered.</p>\n<p>Wound Aid removes Wounds by 1 per every hour of First Aid Action that's given. The Medic may use Biofoam alongside this and increase the Biofoam's healing by half their Intellect Modifier per use. This does not count as the Extended Medical Test needed to allow the patient to begin healing normally and does not reset the uses of Biofoam the Character may receive.</p>\n<p>When given proper equipment, the Medic may have multiple patients at a time that they give these First Aid Extended Actions to. A Character giving First Aid may have up to their Intellect Modifier in Patients that they tend to at a time, without increasing how long it takes to care for everyone involved.</p>\n<h2>Diagnoses</h2>\n<p>With a successful Medication Skill Test, a Medic can diagnose a disease or medical issue. The GM can alter the difficulty of the test for different situations. If a bullet wound causes the issue, it would be a Simple Medical Test. A well known disease could be a +20. The GM may come up with the Difficulty Modifier needed to pass the Diagnosis.</p>\n<p>Each time a Character makes a proper Diagnosis, the next time they come across the same medical issue, they gain a stacking +10 Bonus. Once the character would reach +40 to their Diagnosis Test, they are considered to pass the test automatically.</p>\n<h2>Extended Medical Test</h2>\n<p>The Medication Skill and a Medical Kit is needed to do an Extended Medical Test, where the Character cares for their patient to hasten their healing process and recover from the usage of various drugs, such as Biofoam. Extended Medical Tests take 4 Hours, but is reduced by 1 hour per Degree of Success on a Medication Test, to a minimum of 1. Degrees of Failure will each add an etra 30 Minutes onto the Action.</p>\n<p>The Character who receives an Extended Medical Test will have their natural healing increased. Every 24 hours, the Character will heal their Toughness Modifier worth of Wounds. The Medication Test also increases the number of wounds healed on the first day by the amount of Degrees of Success the Medic rolled.</p>\n<p>Characters who receive Extended Medical Tests will continue to receive them each day, up to the Medic's Intellect Modifier in days, but only if they rest. Characters who take actions such as Charge, Run, or Full Actions of Attacks will lose the next following days of the Extended Medical Test.</p>\n<h2>Alien Biology</h2>\n<p>There are many races, most of which share a completely alien biology compared to each other. Any Medication Tests made against an alien, without the proper Skill, is at a -60, including the Untrained Penalty.</p>"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"an9AAnyv69VtBEmg":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.4V5BCZiFRPSneoas"}},"_id":"ByYVy9fOi4YRXKFV"}
