{"name":"Navigation (Ground/Air)","type":"skill","img":"icons/environment/wilderness/island.webp","data":{"difficulty":"basic","type":"field","cost":{"trained":"200","plus10":"400","plus20":"600"},"stat":{"str":false,"tou":false,"agi":false,"wfr":false,"wfm":false,"int":true,"per":true,"cr":false,"ch":false,"ld":false},"description":"<p>The Navigation Skill is a character's ability to plot courses and find directions. There are multiple levels of Navigation: Ground/Air, Space, and Slipspace.</p>\n<p><em>There is equipment in other Splat books that makes Navigation easy, if not instantly giving all of the information needed to the character. If, for some reason, a character's TACNAV or other GPS systems are not working, then this will be needed. You cannot have a TACNAV or GPS map if you are in uncharted territory.</em></p>"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"an9AAnyv69VtBEmg":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.sP71QmoCimORJdjf"}},"_id":"PhlybStSn0J4OdS2"}
