{"name":"Navigation (Slipspace)","type":"skill","img":"icons/magic/movement/portal-vortex-orange.webp","data":{"difficulty":"basic","type":"field","cost":{"trained":"400","plus10":"800","plus20":"1000"},"stat":{"str":false,"tou":false,"agi":false,"wfr":false,"wfm":false,"int":true,"per":true,"cr":false,"ch":false,"ld":false},"description":"<p>The Navigation Skill is a character's ability to plot courses and find directions. There are multiple levels of Navigation: Ground/Air, Space, and Slipspace.</p>\n<p><em>There is equipment in other Splat books that makes Navigation easy, if not instantly giving all of the information needed to the character. If, for some reason, a character's TACNAV or other GPS systems are not working, then this will be needed. You cannot have a TACNAV or GPS map if you are in uncharted territory.</em></p>\n<p>When it comes to Slipspace Navigation, only the smartest and most invested of characters can learn. This is due to Slipspace having four dimensions, rather than the three of normal space. Slipspace is completely black and takes incredibly difficult and long mathematical equations to evaluate and navigate.</p>"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"an9AAnyv69VtBEmg":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.qE2sZy648hW2mg36"}},"_id":"SlsGPFFDyKF2dutj"}
{"name":"Negotiation","type":"skill","img":"icons/skills/social/diplomacy-handshake.webp","data":{"difficulty":"basic","type":"social","cost":{"trained":"200","plus10":"400","plus20":"600"},"stat":{"str":false,"tou":false,"agi":false,"wfr":false,"wfm":false,"int":true,"per":false,"cr":false,"ch":true,"ld":false},"description":"<p>The Negotiation Skill is used to strike barters and create deals with others. This skill allows characters to negotiate better prices or outcomes for goods and services. All Negotiation tests are opposed, as they involve interaction. For every degree of success the character gets, the price of an item is reduced by 5%. Failing gives no penalties.</p>\n<p>Negotiation can also be used to deal with hostage situations and dealing with demands. This works as a normal Opposed Test against Charisma and Intellect based Negotiation Skill Tests.</p>"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"an9AAnyv69VtBEmg":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.aUHmtwtd4pT6bebR"}},"_id":"P66frH8yL6LWvJxZ"}
