{"name":"Security","type":"skill","img":"icons/sundries/misc/lock-steel-blue.webp","data":{"difficulty":"adv","type":"field","cost":{"trained":"300","plus10":"500","plus20":"700"},"stat":{"str":false,"tou":false,"agi":false,"wfr":false,"wfm":false,"int":true,"per":false,"cr":false,"ch":false,"ld":false},"description":"<p>The Security Skill is how a Character creates, bypasses, and can spot locks, traps, and security systems. Security is the action of creating and disabling physical objects, like disabling a trip wire, lock-picking doors, or even something like spacing security cameras to properly cover a location. Most any mechanical and primitive trap will also count towards a Security Skill Test.</p>\n<p>If a Character sets up a Security system and another attempts to disable it, this would result in an Opposed Security Test.</p>\n<p>The more advanced the trap is, the more difficult it may be to disable it. The GM must come up with proper modifiers for the Test.</p>\n<table style=\"width: 98.6248%; height: 96px;\" border=\"1\">\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<th style=\"width: 16.449%; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">MOD</th>\n<th style=\"width: 83.1526%; height: 16px;\">EXAMPLE</th>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 16.449%; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">+60</td>\n<td style=\"width: 83.1526%; height: 16px; text-align: left;\">Placing a basic lock strategically.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 16.449%; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">+10</td>\n<td style=\"width: 83.1526%; height: 16px; text-align: left;\">Setting up a trip wire.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 16.449%; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">0</td>\n<td style=\"width: 83.1526%; height: 16px; text-align: left;\">Opening a standard lock.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 16.449%; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">-10</td>\n<td style=\"width: 83.1526%; height: 16px; text-align: left;\">Unlocking a more advanced lock.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 16.449%; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">-20</td>\n<td style=\"width: 83.1526%; height: 16px; text-align: left;\">Trying to take down a computer system that does not have an AI.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"an9AAnyv69VtBEmg":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.zaxh7jvE607tIfND"}},"_id":"EnwCHZnk8B6Tk1UO"}
{"name":"Stunting","type":"skill","img":"icons/skills/movement/figure-running-gray.webp","data":{"difficulty":"basic","type":"move","cost":{"trained":"200","plus10":"400","plus20":"600"},"stat":{"str":false,"tou":false,"agi":true,"wfr":false,"wfm":false,"int":false,"per":false,"cr":false,"ch":false,"ld":false},"description":"<p>The Stunting Skill is used for many things that involve using tricky movement, ramping, and anything that involves incredible concentration to pull off. While under Combat, Stunting works well with merging multiple half actions such as taking a shot while falling or jumping out of a moving vehicle and landing on a specific point.</p>\n<p>The GM should always come up with a modifier for the skill. Examples will be shown below.</p>\n<table style=\"width: 98.6248%;\" border=\"1\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<th style=\"width: 19.612%;\">MOD</th>\n<th style=\"width: 79.9896%;\">EXAMPLE</th>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 19.612%;\">+40</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: left; width: 79.9896%;\">Doing a donut or burning out in a vehicle.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 19.612%;\">+20</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: left; width: 79.9896%;\">Stopping quickly with a turn without flipping the vehicle.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 19.612%;\">0</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: left; width: 79.9896%;\">Jumping off a building and taking a shot at an opponent.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 19.612%;\">-20</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: left; width: 79.9896%;\">Jumping off a moving vehicle onto a specific target.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 19.612%;\">-40</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: left; width: 79.9896%;\">Attempting to ramp off of a ruined building and land on a specific small point.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"an9AAnyv69VtBEmg":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.cmcikDifq9D4Bgth"}},"_id":"cnkJdCu2FQGuH6IH"}
{"name":"Survival","type":"skill","img":"icons/environment/wilderness/camp-improvised.webp","data":{"difficulty":"basic","type":"field","cost":{"trained":"200","plus10":"400","plus20":"600"},"stat":{"str":false,"tou":false,"agi":false,"wfr":false,"wfm":false,"int":true,"per":true,"cr":false,"ch":false,"ld":false},"description":"<p>The Survival Skill allows a characters to endure harsh situations and find answers to bad situations. Survival allows characters to find edible plants, construct viable shelters, determine whether water is safe or not, and many other situations.</p>\n<p>Survival also lets characters track others by following signs left of fleeing or hiding opponents. Tracking can be used similar to @Compendium[world.skills.90Bjg0xEU9HrLQJQ]{Investigation}. Cunning opponents may attempt to use Camouflage to erase their tracks, in which case the character will need to use Investigation Skill Tests to find the tracks, and then Survival Tracking tests take over to continue finding and following the trail. Inquiry may be used to ask nearby passerby if the opponent was seen.</p>"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"an9AAnyv69VtBEmg":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.tUke6IEs8jvZ5nWd"}},"_id":"qn0g2ZyeGynUZHVt"}
{"name":"Technology (Human)","type":"skill","img":"icons/commodities/tech/blueprint.webp","data":{"difficulty":"adv","type":"field","cost":{"trained":"200","plus10":"400","plus20":"600"},"stat":{"str":false,"tou":false,"agi":false,"wfr":false,"wfm":false,"int":true,"per":false,"cr":false,"ch":false,"ld":false},"description":"<p>The Technology Skill permits the character to use and repair equipment and vehicles. Using a basic piece of equipment should not require a Technology Skill Test. Using unusual equipment or advanced technology should require a Technology Skill Test.</p>\n<p>When attempting to repair something, the character will need proper equipment or will not be able to make the test.</p>\n<table style=\"width: 98.6248%;\" border=\"1\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<th style=\"width: 17.9959%;\">MOD</th>\n<th style=\"width: 81.6057%;\">EXAMPLE</th>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 17.9959%;\">+30</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: left; width: 81.6057%;\">Repairing a simple device such as an antenna or installing computer hardware.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 17.9959%;\">+20</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: left; width: 81.6057%;\">Repairing or removing parts of a vehicle when the proper tools are on hand.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 17.9959%;\">+10</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: left; width: 81.6057%;\">Equipping a weapon attachment that has been damaged.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 17.9959%;\">0</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: left; width: 81.6057%;\">Using a scanner for the first time.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 17.9959%;\">-10</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: left; width: 81.6057%;\">Repairing damaged equipment without all of the proper tools.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 17.9959%;\">-20</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: left; width: 81.6057%;\">Attempting to use modern technology for the first time.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 17.9959%;\">-30</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: left; width: 81.6057%;\">Repairing advanced technology without all of the proper tools or knowledge.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<h2>Repairs</h2>\n<p>Characters repairing equipment should generally be used in Narrative Structure, as they can take a long time to perform.</p>\n<p>Even the quickest repairs would take a long time. The following table can be used to give examples of how long it would take to complete repair tasks, listed in minutes.</p>\n<table style=\"width: 98.6248%;\" border=\"1\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<th style=\"width: 18.9191%;\">TIME (MINS)</th>\n<th style=\"width: 80.6825%;\">EXAMPLE</th>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 18.9191%;\">20</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: left; width: 80.6825%;\">Changing a tire on a vehicle.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 18.9191%;\">240</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: left; width: 80.6825%;\">Repairing or replacing a tank tread.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 18.9191%;\">20</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: left; width: 80.6825%;\">Repairing up to 10 Break Points for armor, equipment, or weapons.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 18.9191%;\">10</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: left; width: 80.6825%;\">Replacing a part in equipment.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>Though, characters can assist in repairs to reduce the time it takes. Not all actions can have a ton of Characters assisting. For example, a GM should only allow up to 3 Characters assisting in changing or repairing a tank tread. The GM should discuss with the players how a Character is assisting before allowing the time reduction.</p>\n<p>For every Character assisting with a Repair, the Repair time is divided by that much. For example, a 20 minute process with two Characters will only take 10 minutes, but with 3 Characters, it would take 7 minutes.</p>"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"an9AAnyv69VtBEmg":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.KKIG5Gwz1t1nPTTI"}},"_id":"AOvIvJmP7RpFwAF3"}
