{"name":"Technology (Forerunner)","type":"skill","img":"icons/commodities/tech/tube-chamber-lightning.webp","data":{"difficulty":"adv","type":"field","cost":{"trained":"200","plus10":"400","plus20":"600"},"stat":{"str":false,"tou":false,"agi":false,"wfr":false,"wfm":false,"int":true,"per":false,"cr":false,"ch":false,"ld":false},"description":"<p>The Technology Skill permits the character to use and repair equipment and vehicles. Using a basic piece of equipment should not require a Technology Skill Test. Using unusual equipment or advanced technology should require a Technology Skill Test.</p>\n<p>When attempting to repair something, the character will need proper equipment or will not be able to make the test.</p>\n<table style=\"width: 98.6248%;\" border=\"1\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<th style=\"width: 17.9959%;\">MOD</th>\n<th style=\"width: 81.6057%;\">EXAMPLE</th>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 17.9959%;\">+30</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: left; width: 81.6057%;\">Repairing a simple device such as an antenna or installing computer hardware.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 17.9959%;\">+20</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: left; width: 81.6057%;\">Repairing or removing parts of a vehicle when the proper tools are on hand.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 17.9959%;\">+10</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: left; width: 81.6057%;\">Equipping a weapon attachment that has been damaged.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 17.9959%;\">0</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: left; width: 81.6057%;\">Using a scanner for the first time.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 17.9959%;\">-10</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: left; width: 81.6057%;\">Repairing damaged equipment without all of the proper tools.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 17.9959%;\">-20</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: left; width: 81.6057%;\">Attempting to use modern technology for the first time.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 17.9959%;\">-30</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: left; width: 81.6057%;\">Repairing advanced technology without all of the proper tools or knowledge.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<h2>Repairs</h2>\n<p>Characters repairing equipment should generally be used in Narrative Structure, as they can take a long time to perform.</p>\n<p>Even the quickest repairs would take a long time. The following table can be used to give examples of how long it would take to complete repair tasks, listed in minutes.</p>\n<table style=\"width: 98.6248%;\" border=\"1\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<th style=\"width: 18.9191%;\">TIME (MINS)</th>\n<th style=\"width: 80.6825%;\">EXAMPLE</th>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 18.9191%;\">20</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: left; width: 80.6825%;\">Changing a tire on a vehicle.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 18.9191%;\">240</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: left; width: 80.6825%;\">Repairing or replacing a tank tread.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 18.9191%;\">20</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: left; width: 80.6825%;\">Repairing up to 10 Break Points for armor, equipment, or weapons.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 18.9191%;\">10</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: left; width: 80.6825%;\">Replacing a part in equipment.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>Though, characters can assist in repairs to reduce the time it takes. Not all actions can have a ton of Characters assisting. For example, a GM should only allow up to 3 Characters assisting in changing or repairing a tank tread. The GM should discuss with the players how a Character is assisting before allowing the time reduction.</p>\n<p>For every Character assisting with a Repair, the Repair time is divided by that much. For example, a 20 minute process with two Characters will only take 10 minutes, but with 3 Characters, it would take 7 minutes.</p>"},"effects